overview: Ross joined SurveyMonkey in August 2011 and oversees the Customer Operations organization and Portland, OR office. Previously he spent four years in a variety of leadership roles at Google, most recently leading Chrome distribution. Before that Ross was a Senior Manager within Consumer Operations, leading cross-product efforts in Asia while building global teams responsible for Android and Googleâ€™s Mobile products. Before Google, Ross worked as a Corporate Strategy Manager at Brunswick Corporation and Principal Director at Human Factors International, a user experience consulting group. Ross holds a BS degree in Human Factors Engineering from Tufts University and an MBA from the Fuqua School of Business at Duke University.
